TotalEnergies Q4: Sales And EPS Beat, 2025 Outlook Signals Growth In LNG & Hydrocarbons
data.description: TotalEnergies reports Q4 earnings, beats estimates with $1.90 adjusted EPS. Sales of $52.51B exceed consensus. Company proposes €3.22/share dividend. Outlook: 2.5-2.55 Mboe/d hydrocarbon production in Q1 FY25, 3% production growth in 2025, over 40 Mt of LNG sales, 5% energy production increase, net investments of $17B-$17.5B in FY25.

data.title: Cencora Q1 Earnings: Revenue And EPS Beat On Strong Push From Obesity Drugs, Specialty Medicines
data.description: Cencora posted Q1 sales of $81.5 billion, exceeding forecasts, with strong GLP-1 drug sales. Adjusted EPS beat estimates, and FY25 guidance was raised.

data.title: US Services Growth Slows In January As Tariff Concerns Mount
data.description: The U.S. services sector continued to grow in January 2025, though at a slower pace than expected, highlighting uncertainty as businesses brace for potential tariff impacts.
